<h2>Recursive Sequence Summation</h2><div id="problem_icons" class="noprint"><a href="minimal=918"><img src="images/icons/file_html.png" title="Show HTML problem content" class="icon"></a>&nbsp;<span class="tooltip"><img src="images/icons/info.png" class="icon"><span class="tooltiptext_right">Published on Sunday, 24th November 2024, 04:00 am; Solved by 1121;<br>Difficulty rating: 10%</span></span></div><div id="problem_info"><h3>Problem 918</h3></div>
<div class="problem_content" role="problem">
<p>
The sequence $a_n$ is defined by $a_1=1$, and then recursively for $n\geq1$:
\begin{align*}
a_{2n}  &amp;=2a_n\\
a_{2n+1} &amp;=a_n-3a_{n+1}
\end{align*}
The first ten terms are $1, 2, -5, 4, 17, -10, -17, 8, -47, 34$.<br>
Define $\displaystyle S(N) = \sum_{n=1}^N a_n$. You are given $S(10) = -13$.<br>
Find $S(10^{12})$.
</p>
</div><br>
